WEBVTT

00:02.656 --> 00:04.212
Richard: A month ago,
you were in med school

00:04.271 --> 00:06.287
being taught
by doctors.

00:06.372 --> 00:10.201
Today
you are the doctors.

00:10.286 --> 00:12.717
The seven years you spend here
as a surgical resident

00:12.802 --> 00:14.943
will be the best
and worst of your life.

00:15.234 --> 00:16.549
[ Reuben and the Dark's
"Shiny Happy People" plays ]

00:16.633 --> 00:19.024
<i>♪ Da, da, dum, da, dum ♪</i>

00:19.109 --> 00:20.813
- [ Groans ]
<i>- ♪ Da, da, dum, da, dum ♪</i>

00:20.898 --> 00:23.255
Meredith: <i>There's an old joke
doctors like to tell.</i>

00:23.340 --> 00:24.586
[ Motor whirring ]

00:24.671 --> 00:26.128
"Hey, Doc, it hurts
when I go

00:26.220 --> 00:28.446
- like this."
<i>- ♪ Da, da, dum, da, dum ♪</i>

00:28.531 --> 00:30.291
<i>♪ Da, da, dum, da, dum ♪</i>

00:30.376 --> 00:33.231
And the doctor says,
"Well, don't go like this."

00:34.413 --> 00:37.310
♪ Meet me in the crowd ♪

00:37.395 --> 00:41.030
It's a lame joke,
but it's nonetheless true.

00:41.523 --> 00:43.693
- ♪ People, people ♪
- Okay, folks. Meeting time.

00:43.778 --> 00:46.617
Please take your seats.
♪ Throw your love around ♪

00:46.702 --> 00:48.639
<i>As human beings,
we can't help</i>

00:48.724 --> 00:50.654
<i>but want to follow
our instincts...</i>

00:50.739 --> 00:52.222
<i>♪ Love me, love me ♪</i>

00:52.497 --> 00:54.350
- Hey!
<i>- ♪ Take it into town ♪</i>

00:54.435 --> 00:55.615
I, uh,
went back to the loft

00:55.700 --> 00:56.831
and got you another bag
of your stuff.

00:56.915 --> 00:59.653
Oh. Couldn't find those ugly,
fuzzy socks you like.

01:00.011 --> 01:01.078
<i>♪ Happy, happy ♪</i>

01:01.163 --> 01:02.724
...to follow our guts...

01:02.934 --> 01:04.663
- That face is over socks?
<i>- ♪ Put it in the ground ♪</i>

01:04.747 --> 01:05.843
...our primal urges...

01:06.098 --> 01:11.245
Uh, some bills, some junk,
and, uh, top letter.

01:11.846 --> 01:15.852
<i>♪ Everyone around ♪</i>

01:16.214 --> 01:18.113
<i>♪ Love them, love them ♪</i>

01:18.198 --> 01:20.675
...no matter how much
it may hurt.

01:21.056 --> 01:25.606
<i>♪ Put it in your hands ♪</i>

01:25.691 --> 01:29.932
<i>♪ Take it, take it ♪</i>

01:30.198 --> 01:34.432
<i>♪ There's no time to cry ♪</i>

01:34.933 --> 01:38.972
<i>♪ Happy, happy ♪</i>

01:39.355 --> 01:42.762
<i>♪ Put it in your heart ♪</i>

01:43.136 --> 01:47.222
<i>♪ Where tomorrow shines ♪</i>

01:47.433 --> 01:50.336
[♪♪]

01:50.675 --> 01:56.852
♪ Shiny,
happy people laughing ♪

01:57.214 --> 01:59.523
I'll sit with you.
We can read it together.

01:59.623 --> 02:00.948
I got it.

02:01.839 --> 02:03.512
I got it.

02:03.839 --> 02:05.852
<i>♪ Da, da, dum, da, dum ♪</i>

02:06.222 --> 02:08.800
<i>- ♪ Da, da, dum, da, dum ♪</i>
- You know where to find me.

02:08.886 --> 02:12.552
[♪♪]

02:12.863 --> 02:15.403
<i>♪ Da, da, dum, da, dum ♪</i>

02:15.488 --> 02:17.722
<i>♪ Da, da, dum, da, dum ♪</i>

02:17.806 --> 02:20.892
[♪♪]

02:21.299 --> 02:27.551
<i>♪ Shiny, happy people
holding hands ♪</i>

02:27.636 --> 02:32.972
[♪♪]

02:33.056 --> 02:38.863
<i>♪ Shiny, happy people
laughing ♪</i>

02:38.948 --> 02:41.432
[♪♪]

02:41.855 --> 02:42.988
Alex: <i>Dear Jo...</i>

02:43.073 --> 02:44.432
[♪♪]

02:45.405 --> 02:49.561
<i>Mer, this is not
the way I wanted to do this.</i>

02:49.713 --> 02:54.425
<i>Dear Dr. Bailey, I regret to
inform you, blah, blah, blah,</i>

02:54.516 --> 02:57.001
<i>that I will not be
returning to Grey-Sloan.</i>

02:58.056 --> 03:01.079
<i>The last thing on Earth
I want to do is hurt you,</i>

03:01.696 --> 03:03.555
<i>but I'm leaving.</i>

03:04.157 --> 03:06.335
<i>I already left, actually.</i>

03:07.258 --> 03:08.607
<i>I'm gone.</i>

03:08.941 --> 03:10.941
<font color=#FF00FF>*GREY'S ANATOMY*</font>
<font color=#00FF00>Season 16  Episode 16</font>

03:11.026 --> 03:13.041
Episode Title: <font color=#FFc30f>"Leave a Light On"</font>
Aired on: <font color=#00ffff>03/05/2020</font>

03:13.313 --> 03:16.024
[♪♪]
<font color=#ffc30f>Synchronized</font> by <font color=#00FF00>srjanapala</font>

03:16.736 --> 03:20.319
<i>This is not the way I wanted to
do this, but you know me.</i>

03:20.517 --> 03:22.803
<i>Any chance
to take the easy way out.</i>

03:22.904 --> 03:24.882
<i>Or maybe that used to be true.
I don't know.</i>

03:24.967 --> 03:26.428
God, I hate nurses.

03:28.368 --> 03:31.639
I'm Alex.
I'm with Jeremy.

03:31.724 --> 03:33.393
You're, uh... You're with
the Nazi, right?

03:33.478 --> 03:34.932
She may not have pneumonia,
you know?

03:35.017 --> 03:37.103
She could be splinting,
or have a P.E.

03:37.303 --> 03:39.889
Like I said,
I hate nurses.

03:40.196 --> 03:42.032
What did you just say?

03:42.876 --> 03:44.452
Did you just
call me a nurse?

03:44.595 --> 03:46.314
Well,
if the white cap fits.

03:46.414 --> 03:48.571
Alex: <i>What I do know is
I owe you the truth,</i>

03:49.267 --> 03:51.108
<i>and I don't know how else
to tell you.</i>

03:52.442 --> 03:55.781
<i>But you know as well as I do
if I showed up on your doorstep,</i>

03:55.866 --> 03:58.000
<i>you'd yell
or give me guilt or crap</i>

03:58.085 --> 04:00.710
<i>or whatever you do that
seems to always set me straight.</i>

04:00.795 --> 04:01.999
We're grown-ups.

04:02.248 --> 04:03.261
We can't run.

04:03.346 --> 04:05.460
We have to face up to
the stupid things we do.

04:05.545 --> 04:07.233
- Alex!
- Get off!

04:07.506 --> 04:09.265
Supposedly, if you
face up to them,

04:09.350 --> 04:11.500
something good comes out of it.
I don't know what.

04:11.585 --> 04:13.914
You were always the one
to set me straight...

04:13.999 --> 04:16.096
God, I smell good!

04:17.678 --> 04:19.312
You know what it is?

04:19.795 --> 04:22.602
It's the smell
of open-heart surgery.

04:22.686 --> 04:23.812
[ Sniffs ]

04:23.928 --> 04:26.506
It's awesome.
It is awesome.

04:26.843 --> 04:30.063
- You gotta smell me.
- I don't want to smell you.

04:30.148 --> 04:31.752
Alex: ...to point out when I was
being an ass. - Oh, yes, you do.

04:31.836 --> 04:33.996
You have got
to be kidding me!

04:34.578 --> 04:37.868
Okay, I have more important
things to deal with than you.

04:38.024 --> 04:41.533
I have roommates and boy
problems and family problems.

04:41.618 --> 04:44.423
You wanna act like a little
frat-boy bitch? That's fine.

04:44.508 --> 04:47.298
You wanna take credit for
your saves and everybody else's?

04:47.383 --> 04:50.150
That's fine, too.
Just stay outta my face.

04:50.235 --> 04:51.312
And for the record,

04:51.396 --> 04:53.822
you smell like crap!

04:53.907 --> 04:55.197
Alex:
<i>And when that didn't work,</i>

04:55.282 --> 04:57.572
<i>you'd flop in my bed
and say the one perfect thing</i>

04:57.657 --> 04:59.431
<i>that would make sense.</i>

04:59.516 --> 05:03.111
<i>But the thing is,
I can't come back.</i>

05:03.196 --> 05:06.722
[♪♪]

05:06.946 --> 05:08.182
<i>I can't face you.</i>

05:08.266 --> 05:10.079
You can go.

05:11.023 --> 05:12.400
What are you gonna do
if I leave?

05:12.485 --> 05:14.142
It's just us now.

05:14.227 --> 05:17.337
There were five of us,
and now it's just you and I.

05:17.422 --> 05:18.762
And it can't be just me.

05:18.846 --> 05:20.095
It seems like
five seconds ago,

05:20.180 --> 05:21.312
we were the interns
hiding in the tunnels.

05:21.396 --> 05:23.052
- Alex!
- Get off.

05:23.136 --> 05:24.548
Look, I'm not gonna stay
in Seattle

05:24.633 --> 05:26.010
just because you don't want
to be alone.

05:26.094 --> 05:28.650
<i>I deserve the guilt
and to be called an ass,</i>

05:28.735 --> 05:30.945
<i>but I don't want to be
set straight.</i>

05:31.136 --> 05:33.352
<i>I don't want you
to say the right thing</i>

05:33.782 --> 05:36.523
<i>because the one perfect thing
isn't in Seattle.</i>

05:36.952 --> 05:38.382
<i>Not anymore.</i>

05:38.766 --> 05:40.915
Yang left me
her shares and her board seat

05:41.031 --> 05:43.679
and... she left me you,
too.

05:44.077 --> 05:45.378
It's just us now.

05:46.039 --> 05:47.962
I don't know... if you need
somebody to bitch to

05:48.164 --> 05:49.836
or just be...

05:50.875 --> 05:52.472
My person.

05:53.172 --> 05:54.428
I don't know
what you mean.

05:54.796 --> 05:56.118
But you do.

05:56.203 --> 05:57.861
Alex: Apparently,
I'm your emergency contact.

05:57.945 --> 05:59.860
I want waffle Sundays.

05:59.952 --> 06:01.749
Like a family,
all of us...

06:01.835 --> 06:04.291
Everybody, all together.

06:04.376 --> 06:05.234
Okay.

06:05.342 --> 06:06.961
I want to do that
as long as we can.

06:07.756 --> 06:10.671
- It's important to me.
- God, get off! Stop it!

06:10.817 --> 06:14.483
[ Laughing ] Oh, my God.
Ohh.

06:14.734 --> 06:17.531
[ Both laugh ]

06:17.616 --> 06:21.062
<i>But I swear, it's not
about work or you or Jo.</i>

06:21.355 --> 06:23.231
<i>It's about me.</i>

06:23.417 --> 06:24.812
<i>I left.</i>

06:26.326 --> 06:27.914
And I'm with Izzie.

06:28.046 --> 06:30.756
[♪♪]

06:32.647 --> 06:35.250
Alex: <i>This is probably the part
where you're gonna get on your phone</i>

06:35.334 --> 06:36.671
<i>and call a million times</i>

06:36.818 --> 06:39.013
<i>and leave hateful messages
on my machine</i>

06:39.131 --> 06:40.967
<i>till I call you back.</i>

06:41.217 --> 06:42.787
<i>But I can't, Mer.</i>

06:43.122 --> 06:45.214
<i>I can't lie to you,
and I can't promise</i>

06:45.315 --> 06:48.101
<i>I'm gonna come home
because it's not home anymore.</i>

06:48.332 --> 06:50.248
- Go make her happy.
- Yeah.

06:50.591 --> 06:55.248
[♪♪]

06:55.459 --> 06:57.795
[ Cheering, whistling ]

06:57.880 --> 06:59.636
[♪♪]

06:59.721 --> 07:02.377
<i>When you were in danger
of losing your license,</i>

07:02.477 --> 07:04.013
<i>when I called everyone
to write letters</i>

07:04.098 --> 07:05.959
<i>and show up on your behalf,</i>

07:07.189 --> 07:08.568
<i>I called Izzie, too.</i>

07:10.394 --> 07:12.370
<i>I want to say
I hoped she wouldn't answer,</i>

07:12.471 --> 07:15.599
<i>but the truth is
I hoped she would.</i>

07:16.021 --> 07:18.701
<i>I want to say,
"I had to call her for you,"</i>

07:18.950 --> 07:20.786
<i>but that would be a lie.</i>

07:20.970 --> 07:23.052
<i>The truth is
your trial gave me</i>

07:23.137 --> 07:25.183
<i>an excuse good enough
to call her.</i>

07:25.462 --> 07:27.413
[ Monitor flatlines ]

07:27.552 --> 07:30.107
<i>'Cause I wanted to know
where she landed.</i>

07:30.325 --> 07:33.169
- [ Ingrid Michaelson's "Turn to Stone" plays]
- Alex: <i>Today is the day my life begins.</i>

07:33.253 --> 07:35.088
<i>All my life,
I've been just me...</i>

07:35.173 --> 07:37.236
<i>Just a smart-mouth kid.</i>

07:38.646 --> 07:41.181
<i>- ♪ Beyond a story book ♪
- Today I become a man.</i>

07:41.942 --> 07:43.838
Today I become a husband.

07:44.744 --> 07:47.806
Today I become accountable
to someone other than myself.

07:47.891 --> 07:49.951
<i>♪ And learn our souls
are all we own ♪</i>

07:50.036 --> 07:52.490
<i>Today I become accountable
to you,</i>

07:52.590 --> 07:54.310
<i>to our future,</i>

07:54.733 --> 07:57.959
to all the possibilities
that our marriage has to offer.

07:58.129 --> 08:00.638
Together,
no matter what happens,

08:01.264 --> 08:02.354
I'll be ready...

08:02.676 --> 08:05.248
I wanted to know
if she was alive and well.

08:05.333 --> 08:06.518
- [ Alarms beeping ]
- Richard: <i>Screw the DNR.</i>

08:06.602 --> 08:08.150
- <i>Hand me those paddles.</i>
- [ Crying ]

08:08.235 --> 08:10.639
- Clear.
- <i>I wanted to hear her voice.</i>

08:10.732 --> 08:14.198
[ Singsong voice ]
I'm a bride. [ Laughs ]

08:14.283 --> 08:17.360
- Iz, come on. I'm getting her a real one.
- [ Normal voice ] I love this one,

08:17.444 --> 08:19.150
and that makes it
a real one.

08:19.235 --> 08:21.571
Alex: <i>When she picked up,
I blurted out the whole thing</i>

08:21.656 --> 08:23.713
<i>about you picking up trash
off the street</i>

08:23.798 --> 08:26.038
<i>and needing a letter that proved
you're better than that.</i>

08:26.907 --> 08:28.271
<i>[ Chuckles ]
And she laughed and said,</i>

08:28.355 --> 08:29.691
<i>"Of course she'd be
trash-picking,</i>

08:29.783 --> 08:31.449
<i>trying to save the world."</i>

08:31.604 --> 08:34.520
Today, Izzie Stevens,
our life together begins.

08:34.900 --> 08:36.813
<i>And I, for one,
can't wait.</i>

08:37.010 --> 08:38.756
<i>And then these voices
were in the background</i>

08:38.841 --> 08:40.477
<i>and a girl was singing
this song about</i>

08:40.563 --> 08:43.979
<i>"greasy, grimy gopher guts"
that I learned in first grade</i>

08:44.143 --> 08:49.179
<i>and I started laughing and
I asked if she had kids and...</i>

08:49.264 --> 08:51.104
<i>Izzie got quiet.
[ Girl speaks indistinctly ]</i>

08:51.703 --> 08:53.454
<i>For so long, she was quiet,</i>

08:53.569 --> 08:56.525
<i>and finally, she said,
"Yeah, I have kids."</i>

08:56.610 --> 08:58.316
[ Children giggle ]

08:58.439 --> 09:00.186
<i>- "Twins."
- ♪ I know that I am nothing new ♪</i>

09:00.270 --> 09:04.228
<i>And it turns out
they're my kids, Mer.</i>

09:05.128 --> 09:11.004
<i>- ♪ There's so much more than me and you ♪
- Izzie's and my kids.</i>

09:11.462 --> 09:13.196
<i>She had our kids.</i>

09:13.423 --> 09:20.799
<i>♪ But, brother,
how we must atone ♪</i>

09:20.891 --> 09:27.721
<i>♪ Before we turn to stone ♪</i>

09:30.480 --> 09:32.056
I love Jo.

09:32.172 --> 09:36.134
<i>- Deeply. Still.
- [ Exhales sharply ]</i>

09:36.219 --> 09:37.970
<i>I think I always will.</i>

09:38.439 --> 09:41.071
<i>And if it was just about
two women I love,</i>

09:41.345 --> 09:43.089
<i>I'd choose my wife.</i>

09:43.181 --> 09:44.626
<i>You know I would.</i>

09:44.711 --> 09:46.618
- Hey.
<i>- But it's not just her.</i>

09:46.703 --> 09:47.962
<i>Izzie made our kids.</i>

09:48.047 --> 09:50.963
I snooched into a cup
for you today.

09:51.860 --> 09:55.126
Um... thank you?

09:55.297 --> 09:57.009
<i>She was single
and wanted children</i>

09:57.094 --> 09:59.712
<i>and couldn't have 'em because
the cancer nuked her eggs.</i>

09:59.797 --> 10:02.118
<i>But she had our embryos.</i>

10:03.540 --> 10:04.540
[ Sighs ]

10:04.692 --> 10:05.868
<i>Back then
I was too freaked out</i>

10:05.952 --> 10:09.047
<i>to care about what she did with
them if we never used them.</i>

10:09.132 --> 10:10.679
You think a Dixie cup
full of my swimmers

10:10.763 --> 10:12.009
will make everything okay?

10:12.094 --> 10:17.148
It's crap. This is crap.
[ Sighs ]

10:17.233 --> 10:19.939
You just can't go messing
with people's heads like that.

10:20.024 --> 10:21.610
Even if she freezes
the embryos,

10:21.695 --> 10:23.692
you think... you think
we'll get a chance to use them?

10:23.776 --> 10:25.273
You think
she'll still be here?

10:26.463 --> 10:28.164
You think she'll survive
all this?

10:28.249 --> 10:29.156
Do you think...

10:29.248 --> 10:30.756
She t-told me...

10:30.841 --> 10:33.101
She told me she was seeing
a ghost, okay?

10:33.186 --> 10:35.375
And I'm so used to all
the crazy chicks in my life

10:35.460 --> 10:36.590
that I didn't even...

10:40.846 --> 10:42.222
[ Voice breaking ]
I'm a doctor.

10:42.431 --> 10:44.093
A doctor!

10:46.268 --> 10:47.890
And I didn't even think
to...

10:50.801 --> 10:51.807
And now she's...

10:51.891 --> 10:53.492
This is...

10:54.050 --> 10:55.523
This is wrong.

10:57.101 --> 10:59.053
This isn't
how it's supposed to happen.

10:59.138 --> 11:00.474
I know.

11:00.566 --> 11:02.942
- It's crap.
- I know.

11:03.367 --> 11:04.597
I hate this.

11:04.681 --> 11:05.681
I know.

11:05.769 --> 11:07.059
This isn't...

11:10.514 --> 11:13.480
This isn't how we...
How we were supp...

11:13.565 --> 11:15.007
This isn't how I wanted
to do this.

11:15.099 --> 11:17.515
This isn't how Izzie and I
were supposed to make a baby.

11:17.814 --> 11:19.730
<i>So I signed papers
saying she could do</i>

11:19.815 --> 11:21.601
<i>whatever she wanted
with them.</i>

11:21.686 --> 11:24.102
<i>And so she used them.</i>

11:24.679 --> 11:26.273
<i>And she had twins.</i>

11:26.645 --> 11:28.968
<i>Eli and Alexis.</i>

11:29.200 --> 11:32.366
<i>[ Children shouting
indistinctly ]</i>

11:32.583 --> 11:35.656
<i>I should have told Jo
or told you, but I didn't.</i>

11:35.972 --> 11:38.664
<i>I got through the trial
and then I came here</i>

11:39.132 --> 11:40.637
<i>and I met the kids.</i>

11:40.801 --> 11:45.082
<i>Met my kids, Mer.</i>

11:45.285 --> 11:46.449
<i>They're five.</i>

11:46.534 --> 11:51.160
<i>And hilarious and stubborn
as hell, just like Izzie.</i>

11:51.442 --> 11:52.848
[ Children shouting
indistinctly ]

11:52.933 --> 11:55.082
<i>Like this little team
that gangs up on me</i>

11:55.167 --> 11:57.333
<i>with stubbornness
and sticky hands.</i>

11:57.487 --> 11:59.910
<i>Hi, horsey!
[ Horse whinnies ]</i>

11:59.995 --> 12:02.111
<i>And the second I walked
in the door,</i>

12:02.482 --> 12:04.168
<i>they wanted to show me
their rooms</i>

12:04.253 --> 12:06.512
<i>and the look on their faces
when they were showing me</i>

12:06.597 --> 12:09.013
<i>all their toys and books
and...</i>

12:09.098 --> 12:12.496
<i>asked if they could
call me...</i>

12:12.718 --> 12:14.114
<i>Dad.</i>

12:15.188 --> 12:16.692
<i>They both want to be doctors,</i>

12:16.777 --> 12:19.341
<i>and Izzie teaches them
to bake just like her.</i>

12:19.426 --> 12:21.449
<i>And they scribble
pictures of stethoscopes</i>

12:21.534 --> 12:23.449
<i>all over the walls in chalk.</i>

12:23.902 --> 12:25.645
<i>And Alexis...
[ Girl giggling ]</i>

12:25.752 --> 12:26.996
<i>...oh,
she's got Izzie's eyes.</i>

12:27.081 --> 12:31.270
<i>And... Eli smiles crooked
just like I do.</i>

12:31.355 --> 12:34.846
<i>And now I live on a freaking
farm in Nowhere, Kansas.</i>

12:34.931 --> 12:36.467
<i>[ Chicken clucks ]</i>

12:36.551 --> 12:37.879
[♪♪]

12:38.018 --> 12:39.216
<i>And the kids play
with the chickens</i>

12:39.300 --> 12:42.386
<i>and Izzie goes to work
as a surgical oncologist.</i>

12:42.471 --> 12:44.177
<i>[ Chickens cluck ]</i>

12:44.402 --> 12:46.738
<i>Oh, and she's amazing, Mer.</i>

12:46.971 --> 12:48.567
<i>The progress she's made.</i>

12:48.652 --> 12:49.973
<i>She's alive.</i>

12:50.058 --> 12:52.262
<i>And she's a miracle
and keeping other people alive.</i>

12:52.347 --> 12:54.563
<i>And I'm applying
to the hospital nearby.</i>

12:54.891 --> 12:56.567
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>

12:56.731 --> 12:59.262
<i>And I wanted to be mad at Izzie
for keeping them from me,</i>

12:59.347 --> 13:03.285
<i>but I can't because all I am
is grateful she made them.</i>

13:03.399 --> 13:06.349
<i>Oh, they're so damn smart,
smarter than I was at their age.</i>

13:06.434 --> 13:08.606
<i>Hell, sometimes at my age.
[ Sighs ]</i>

13:08.691 --> 13:10.370
<i>And they get to
have everything...</i>

13:10.692 --> 13:12.967
<i>A home where they feel safe
and loved,</i>

13:13.051 --> 13:14.418
<i>and they play "sleepover,"</i>

13:14.503 --> 13:16.709
<i>where they just keep
swapping beds non-stop,</i>

13:16.794 --> 13:19.090
<i>all night until
they land in ours at 4:00 a.m.</i>

13:19.175 --> 13:20.341
[♪♪]

13:20.426 --> 13:22.382
<i>And they wake up
with two parents,</i>

13:23.004 --> 13:25.217
<i>when I rarely
ever even had one.</i>

13:25.301 --> 13:26.465
<i>Oh, I love them, Mer,</i>

13:26.550 --> 13:28.416
<i>with every inch of me
and every cell,</i>

13:28.501 --> 13:30.215
<i>and I get to be their dad.</i>

13:31.015 --> 13:33.957
<i>I'm the guy who lied
and said I only had one ball</i>

13:34.049 --> 13:35.845
- <i>to get into Seattle Grace.</i>
- [ Laughs ]

13:35.930 --> 13:37.471
<i>And it worked.</i>

13:37.556 --> 13:40.382
<i>I got a job and a career I love
based on a lie</i>

13:40.467 --> 13:43.507
<i>that no one really cared about,
and I made it work.</i>

13:45.199 --> 13:46.878
<i>And when I look at my kids</i>

13:46.963 --> 13:49.709
<i>and doubt if I know
how to do right by them,</i>

13:49.941 --> 13:54.067
<i>I just think of you and Zola
and Bailey and Ellis.</i>

13:54.573 --> 13:56.847
<i>You're so brave. And you've
grown into this incredible mother,</i>

13:56.931 --> 13:58.927
<i>this incredible surgeon.</i>

13:59.011 --> 13:59.967
<i>[ Applause ]</i>

14:00.051 --> 14:01.104
<i>You did that.</i>

14:02.713 --> 14:05.129
<i>You always said Cristina
was your person.</i>

14:05.214 --> 14:07.130
<i>Then I was your person.
[ Monitor flatlines ]</i>

14:07.215 --> 14:10.315
<i>But you've always been
your own damn person,</i>

14:10.518 --> 14:12.987
<i>a force of freaking nature.</i>

14:13.222 --> 14:16.245
<i>You've never needed
anyone but you.</i>

14:16.861 --> 14:18.180
<i>And you can come here,
you know?</i>

14:18.265 --> 14:20.261
<i>You... You...
You could show up at my door</i>

14:20.346 --> 14:22.112
<i>and... and get me
to walk away from all this</i>

14:22.197 --> 14:24.501
<i>and just go back to you
and Jo and the hospital</i>

14:24.586 --> 14:27.066
<i>- and everyone who helped me get here.
- All: ...two... one!</i>

14:27.151 --> 14:29.317
<i>Alex:
But I hope you don't.</i>

14:29.448 --> 14:30.932
<i>Mer,
you are my best friend,</i>

14:31.017 --> 14:32.513
<i>and I will miss the hell
out of you,</i>

14:32.598 --> 14:38.182
<i>but [sighs] I'm finally
exactly where I should be.</i>

14:38.579 --> 14:40.831
<i>I never had that before.</i>

14:41.665 --> 14:45.281
<i>So, I hope you do come here
one day,</i>

14:45.784 --> 14:48.198
<i>but not to ask me to leave.
[ Sniffles ]</i>

14:48.283 --> 14:50.456
<i>I hope you come
to meet my kids</i>

14:50.605 --> 14:52.861
<i>and they get to call you
"Auntie Mer."</i>

14:53.430 --> 14:56.878
<i>Because you'll love them,
and they'll love you.</i>

14:57.072 --> 14:58.854
<i>And until you're ready
to do that,</i>

15:00.266 --> 15:02.262
<i>try not to hate me too much.</i>

15:02.510 --> 15:03.800
<i>Please?</i>

15:05.180 --> 15:08.346
- <i>Alex.</i>
- [ Sniffles ]

15:08.431 --> 15:10.427
[ Sighs ]

15:10.511 --> 15:13.096
[♪♪]

15:13.181 --> 15:14.387
[ Sniffles ]

15:14.551 --> 15:17.511
[♪♪]

15:20.392 --> 15:22.018
Alex: <i>I'm sorry.</i>

15:22.103 --> 15:23.899
[♪♪]

15:24.525 --> 15:26.165
<i>You deserve
more than a letter.</i>

15:26.564 --> 15:27.886
I'm your intern
for the day.

15:27.971 --> 15:30.073
Oh. Well, hello, intern.
You have a name?

15:30.158 --> 15:31.221
Jo Wilson.

15:31.306 --> 15:33.821
Oh, nice. I like chicks
with boys names.

15:34.298 --> 15:35.766
<i>And this right here,</i>

15:35.907 --> 15:39.269
<i>this cowardice, this letter?</i>

15:40.126 --> 15:41.809
<i>It's officially
the worst thing I've ever done.</i>

15:41.893 --> 15:43.923
<i>[ Shouts indistinctly ]</i>

15:44.157 --> 15:46.135
- [ Sighs ]
- <i>But it's about me, Jo.</i>

15:46.220 --> 15:47.134
<i>It's not about you.</i>

15:47.219 --> 15:50.438
- I don't live in my car anymore, jerk.
<i>- It's not what you deserve.</i>

15:50.523 --> 15:53.752
<i>You deserve and have earned so
much better than this. I got you a couch.</i>

15:53.837 --> 15:55.565
[ Mouth full ] Hey,
powdered sugar's your favorite.

15:55.649 --> 15:57.314
Yeah, no.
Uh, this is great.

15:57.399 --> 15:58.649
You wanted to hear me
say the words.

15:58.733 --> 16:02.110
So I'm...
saying them right now.

16:04.436 --> 16:06.242
<i>I love you, Jo.</i>

16:06.687 --> 16:08.714
[ Sighs ] <i>- I love that you
are brilliant and brave,</i>

16:08.798 --> 16:10.345
<i>and no matter
what you go through...</i>

16:10.430 --> 16:11.525
Hey, Brooke.

16:11.611 --> 16:13.142
Oh, wait. It's...
It's "Jo" now, right?

16:13.227 --> 16:14.785
[ Sniffles ]

16:14.992 --> 16:16.907
<i>...you never
let it hold you back.</i>

16:16.992 --> 16:20.126
<i>Do I look like him?
You have my father's eyes...</i>

16:20.211 --> 16:21.462
<i>You have an out.</i>

16:21.547 --> 16:24.610
[ Grunting ]

16:24.695 --> 16:26.688
<i>It makes you stronger,
kinder.</i>

16:27.036 --> 16:28.532
<i>You made me kinder.</i>

16:28.617 --> 16:29.962
<i>That works?
The compliments thing?</i>

16:30.047 --> 16:31.203
Mm-hmm.

16:31.452 --> 16:32.868
God, you're sexy.

16:33.007 --> 16:34.321
Doesn't work on me.

16:34.406 --> 16:35.445
Ohh!
[ Laughs ]

16:35.545 --> 16:38.454
Oh. A little warning
when people are over

16:38.539 --> 16:39.368
would be nice.

16:39.453 --> 16:42.649
<i>You loved me for exactly
who I was, and I loved you.</i>

16:42.734 --> 16:43.979
I'm gonna marry
that girl.

16:44.542 --> 16:46.485
Ohh! [ Gasps ] Yes!

16:46.570 --> 16:47.689
<i>I love you.</i>

16:47.985 --> 16:51.024
<i>Maybe it's not fair to say that,
but it's true.</i>

16:51.570 --> 16:52.189
What's also true is...

16:52.273 --> 16:54.479
[ Breathes sharply ]

16:54.849 --> 16:56.265
...I'm in love with Izzie.

16:56.350 --> 16:58.149
[ Sighs ]

16:58.233 --> 17:02.309
[♪♪]

17:02.826 --> 17:03.992
When I asked you

17:04.077 --> 17:05.508
if you wanted
to move in with me,

17:05.593 --> 17:06.983
you said that you did

17:07.069 --> 17:08.384
and that you could
picture a life with me,

17:08.468 --> 17:10.992
but you never said anything
about babies.

17:11.077 --> 17:14.078
You said,
"Maybe we could get a dog."

17:14.163 --> 17:16.509
- Do you want a dog?
- No, I want to know what we're doing here.

17:16.593 --> 17:18.625
I love you,
and you love me.

17:18.710 --> 17:20.367
I know,
but when I look ahead...

17:20.452 --> 17:21.414
Why are we
looking ahead?

17:21.499 --> 17:23.656
If you had or maybe
you do have, for all I know,

17:23.741 --> 17:26.079
a bunch of Izzie babies walking
around with your face on them...

17:26.163 --> 17:27.351
And why
are we doing it now?

17:27.435 --> 17:29.859
And... And I'm just
the "Let's get a dog" girl?

17:29.944 --> 17:31.968
You always ask about Izzie,
what she was like.

17:32.053 --> 17:33.407
Well, that...
That girl right there.

17:33.491 --> 17:35.054
<i>That... That's what Izzie
was like.</i>

17:35.139 --> 17:38.101
<i>I imagined this whole life
for her where she was baking</i>

17:38.186 --> 17:40.148
<i>and happy
and had a bunch of kids.</i>

17:40.233 --> 17:42.101
Jo: Alex, if you want
to know how she is,

17:42.186 --> 17:43.297
you should just call her.

17:43.382 --> 17:45.172
<i>And I never imagined me
in that picture.</i>

17:45.257 --> 17:46.460
You should call Izzie.

17:46.545 --> 17:48.037
<i>But suddenly, I am.</i>

17:48.615 --> 17:50.769
<i>Not suddenly.
That's a lie there.</i>

17:51.373 --> 17:53.241
<i>There was a part of me
that always wondered,</i>

17:53.326 --> 17:55.077
<i>always [sighs]
wanted to know,</i>

17:55.162 --> 17:58.859
<i>always felt
like we left things unresolved,</i>

17:59.521 --> 18:01.217
<i>unfinished.</i>

18:01.817 --> 18:05.946
<i>So, when Mer needed all those
letters, I reached out to her.</i>

18:06.537 --> 18:08.601
<i>I reached out to Izzie
and we started talking</i>

18:08.686 --> 18:10.507
<i>and it scared the crap
out of me</i>

18:10.592 --> 18:13.439
<i>because it felt like
no time had passed,</i>

18:14.131 --> 18:17.015
<i>like Izzie and I were
kind of frozen together in time,</i>

18:17.100 --> 18:19.744
<i>and now... now we're not.</i>

18:19.829 --> 18:20.835
<i>She's not.</i>

18:20.920 --> 18:22.359
<i>She's here in Kansas,</i>

18:22.443 --> 18:25.359
<i>on a farm in this incredible
place in the middle of nowhere.</i>

18:25.443 --> 18:27.269
<i>And I never,
in a million years,</i>

18:27.353 --> 18:30.439
<i>would think I belong here,
but I do.</i>

18:31.383 --> 18:32.947
<i>- And I can't lie to you...
- [ Horse whinnies ]</i>

18:33.031 --> 18:34.939
<i>...and pretend the truth
isn't the truth...</i>

18:35.024 --> 18:37.461
<i>That I love you
and I love Izzie.</i>

18:38.273 --> 18:42.010
<i>But if it was just me missing
her or nostalgia or whatever...</i>

18:42.095 --> 18:43.002
Will you stay with me?

18:43.087 --> 18:44.727
<i>...I would have been able to
walk away</i>

18:44.812 --> 18:46.062
<i>and come back to you.</i>

18:48.236 --> 18:50.359
- [ Breath shaking ]
<i>- But Izzie had my kids.</i>

18:51.291 --> 18:54.104
<i>And I know you get
what that really means.</i>

18:54.189 --> 18:55.690
<i>I know you of all people</i>

18:55.775 --> 18:58.345
<i>understand why
I can't just leave now...</i>

18:58.494 --> 19:01.809
<i>[ Girl giggling ] ...why I can't miss
another second of my kids' lives.</i>

19:02.509 --> 19:04.689
<i>I have a chance
to make this family whole,</i>

19:05.189 --> 19:08.206
<i>and I just hope you love me back
enough to let me take it.</i>

19:08.291 --> 19:09.359
[ Silverware clanking ]

19:09.572 --> 19:12.362
<i>I need to give these kids
the family you and I never had,</i>

19:12.447 --> 19:16.049
<i>with barbecuing out on
the back porch and soccer games</i>

19:16.134 --> 19:17.978
<i>and movie nights
and book reports.</i>

19:18.311 --> 19:19.804
Both: Mom.

19:19.889 --> 19:26.059
[♪♪]

19:26.335 --> 19:28.390
Alex: <i>I didn't know
she would have my kids,</i>

19:28.475 --> 19:30.317
<i>and now that she does,</i>

19:30.766 --> 19:33.058
<i>I don't know how to look anyone
in the eye if I don't stay</i>

19:33.143 --> 19:36.359
<i>and do everything I can
to make this work...</i>

19:36.952 --> 19:40.280
<i>Make this a life,
make this a family.</i>

19:41.756 --> 19:42.913
<i>You were wrong.</i>

19:43.139 --> 19:45.479
<i>You're not
the "Let's get a dog" girl.</i>

19:45.686 --> 19:47.133
<i>And I was never holding
a candle</i>

19:47.218 --> 19:48.664
<i>or those pieces of paper</i>

19:48.780 --> 19:51.741
<i>thinking anything
would ever change.</i>

19:52.217 --> 19:54.608
<i>When I asked you to marry me,
I meant it.</i>

19:54.693 --> 19:56.469
[ Screaming ]
[ Laughter ]

19:56.554 --> 19:58.485
Alex: <i>And we'll be together
forever, right? You and me.</i>

19:58.569 --> 20:00.328
<i>And if we have kids,
we'll be great.</i>

20:00.413 --> 20:02.099
<i>I'll be a great dad,
and you'll be great,</i>

20:02.183 --> 20:03.765
<i>and it'll be just us.</i>

20:03.850 --> 20:05.836
<i>We won't need anybody else,
okay?</i>

20:05.921 --> 20:09.109
<i>When I told you I love you,
I meant it.</i>

20:09.194 --> 20:12.149
<i>[ Sniffles ]
But Izzie has our kids, Jo.</i>

20:12.825 --> 20:14.304
<i>Our kids.</i>

20:14.514 --> 20:16.899
<i>And the way you and I grew up,
I...</i>

20:17.569 --> 20:19.883
<i>I-I came to meet them,
to start to know them.</i>

20:19.968 --> 20:22.350
<i>I missed five years
of their lives.</i>

20:22.483 --> 20:23.769
<i>And not because I was a junkie
like my dad</i>

20:23.853 --> 20:26.399
<i>or off my meds like my mom.</i>

20:26.991 --> 20:30.019
<i>I didn't exist to them until
I walked through the front door.</i>

20:30.741 --> 20:34.269
<i>And once I did, I had this
family I never knew I had</i>

20:34.353 --> 20:37.939
<i>on this insane farm,
and I wish I'd [sighs]...</i>

20:38.023 --> 20:41.514
<i>I wish getting everything
I always wanted</i>

20:41.599 --> 20:43.928
<i>didn't have to hurt you
in the process.</i>

20:44.013 --> 20:45.019
[♪♪]

20:45.103 --> 20:46.229
[ Sighs ]

20:46.313 --> 20:48.149
[ Sniffles ]

20:48.233 --> 20:52.149
[♪♪]

20:53.677 --> 20:55.154
[ Sighs ]

20:55.239 --> 20:56.859
<i>But I can't lie to you.</i>

20:57.481 --> 20:58.919
<i>And I can't come home.</i>

20:59.153 --> 21:00.786
Alex: Are you asking me
to a dance?

21:00.958 --> 21:04.754
No, I'm... I'm asking you
to come back home.

21:04.989 --> 21:06.383
[♪♪]

21:06.583 --> 21:08.006
<i>I'm not coming home, Jo.</i>

21:08.091 --> 21:09.256
<i>I can't face you.</i>

21:09.341 --> 21:10.490
<i>I can't look you in the eye</i>

21:10.575 --> 21:12.928
<i>because I wouldn't be able to
walk away.</i>

21:13.013 --> 21:15.388
<i>Maybe "I love you"
is wrong to say,</i>

21:15.473 --> 21:19.474
<i>but... thank you
for making me better</i>

21:19.559 --> 21:21.535
<i>and taking care of me
when I needed it,</i>

21:21.691 --> 21:25.332
<i>for taking care of yourself
when you needed it, too.</i>

21:25.832 --> 21:27.208
<i>I went to a lawyer.</i>

21:27.293 --> 21:29.177
<i>I signed divorce papers.</i>

21:29.262 --> 21:31.149
<i>I left everything to you.
It's yours.</i>

21:31.473 --> 21:34.649
<i>You worked for every cent
you ever owned and then some.</i>

21:35.176 --> 21:37.731
<i>I also left you my shares
in Grey-Sloan.</i>

21:37.840 --> 21:41.254
<i>Whatever you choose to do with
them, I know it will be amazing.</i>

21:41.356 --> 21:42.450
<i>Just like you.</i>

21:42.535 --> 21:43.729
[ Sobs ]

21:44.226 --> 21:46.028
<i>You know, I, uh...
[ Clears throat ]</i>

21:46.113 --> 21:48.189
<i>I barely saw you
this week,</i>

21:48.856 --> 21:51.137
<i>and it sucked.</i>

21:52.348 --> 21:55.193
<i>I'll find another job.
Whatever.</i>

21:55.278 --> 21:58.149
<i>I, uh, but I don't want
to never see you again.</i>

21:58.233 --> 22:02.979
<i>Oh, you deserve everything good
in this life, Jo.</i>

22:03.415 --> 22:05.858
<i>I hope you find
so much better than me.</i>

22:06.395 --> 22:07.551
<i>Thank you.</i>

22:08.832 --> 22:10.494
<i>I'm... I'm sorry.</i>

22:11.207 --> 22:13.148
<i>I don't know how to end this.</i>

22:13.957 --> 22:15.348
<i>I don't want to.</i>

22:17.707 --> 22:19.268
<i>Goodbye.</i>

22:20.095 --> 22:22.009
[ Paper rustles ]

22:22.298 --> 22:25.236
[♪♪]

22:26.755 --> 22:29.295
Alex: <i>I'm guessing
you're not surprised by this,</i>

22:29.380 --> 22:31.881
<i>and definitely not happy
about it.</i>

22:32.856 --> 22:34.717
<i>They called me Evil Spawn
most of the time</i>

22:34.802 --> 22:36.084
growing up in your hospital.

22:36.169 --> 22:37.381
Nice panties, Yang.

22:37.465 --> 22:38.591
[ Laughter ]

22:38.675 --> 22:40.711
In your dreams,
Evil Spawn.

22:40.795 --> 22:42.211
It's probably
one of the better nicknames

22:42.295 --> 22:44.591
I had most of my life,
to be honest.

22:44.675 --> 22:46.631
I earned the name.

22:46.715 --> 22:48.817
I know it, you know it.

22:48.902 --> 22:53.791
Morning, people. Hell,
you probably know that better than anyone.

22:53.875 --> 22:56.381
Truth is, you didn't like me
very much in the beginning.

22:56.465 --> 22:58.591
[ Tape rewinds ]

22:59.636 --> 23:01.593
I didn't really like you much,
either.

23:01.678 --> 23:03.398
Sloppy, sloppy, sloppy.

23:03.483 --> 23:06.210
Redo these and return them to me
before lunch, understood?

23:06.295 --> 23:08.203
- Understood.
- Karev, don't tempt me.

23:08.288 --> 23:10.148
And, Karev, see the chief
by the end of the day.

23:10.232 --> 23:10.890
What for?

23:10.975 --> 23:12.832
Do I look psychic to you?
He's the chief.

23:12.917 --> 23:14.092
He asked, you go.

23:14.177 --> 23:15.741
Karev,
go stand in the hall.

23:15.873 --> 23:17.324
- Karev, cover the pit.
- Pit!

23:17.409 --> 23:19.310
<i>Hate being an intern.</i>

23:19.443 --> 23:23.061
<i>You were mean and impatient...
and knew everything,</i>

23:23.146 --> 23:25.077
<i>and you liked everyone else
but me,</i>

23:25.162 --> 23:26.427
<i>even when you pretended
you didn't.</i>

23:26.511 --> 23:28.128
Are you sure
they're balloons?

23:28.644 --> 23:31.136
You have reason to believe
they're not balloons?

23:31.221 --> 23:32.459
This one here's
got a face.

23:32.839 --> 23:34.120
They all do.

23:34.901 --> 23:36.155
I'll be damned.

23:36.417 --> 23:39.004
They're Judys.
Judys?

23:39.355 --> 23:44.074
[ Scoffs ] He swallowed
the heads of ten Judy dolls.

23:44.159 --> 23:46.893
Alex: <i>Or you were convinced
I had "it"...</i>

23:47.198 --> 23:51.042
<i>That something that would make
them great someday.</i>

23:51.143 --> 23:53.840
<i>Hell, you named your kid
after O'Malley.</i>

23:53.925 --> 23:56.050
<i>And Mer named her kid after you,
and you...</i>

23:56.135 --> 23:57.373
[ Whimpers, sighs ]

23:57.611 --> 24:00.746
<i>...you just seemed like all
my other teachers before you</i>

24:00.831 --> 24:03.808
<i>who took one look at me,
decided I was garbage,</i>

24:03.893 --> 24:06.222
<i>and that was
all I'd ever be.</i>

24:06.635 --> 24:08.120
<i>But here's the thing.</i>

24:08.690 --> 24:12.160
<i>Unlike everyone else,
you let me grow the hell up.</i>

24:12.245 --> 24:14.887
- He saved a baby's life.
- <i>You gave me crap when I deserved it.</i>

24:14.972 --> 24:17.472
<i>You pushed my buttons
and my limits when I needed it.</i>

24:17.557 --> 24:20.191
What the hell? You are not some
hotshot surgeon right now.

24:20.276 --> 24:22.307
<i>Yeah, it's a teaching hospital
and all that,</i>

24:22.548 --> 24:25.033
<i>but you did more than that,
and you know it.</i>

24:25.222 --> 24:27.807
Why is there a trailer
in my parking spot?

24:28.026 --> 24:30.433
Is one of these yours?
My bad.

24:30.533 --> 24:32.136
<i>And, sure,
it'd be pretty great</i>

24:32.221 --> 24:33.769
<i>if I just
stayed there forever</i>

24:33.877 --> 24:36.214
<i>and repaid you
for everything you did for me.</i>

24:37.415 --> 24:39.582
<i>But you and I both know
I can't.</i>

24:41.229 --> 24:42.901
<i>Never could.</i>

24:43.244 --> 24:45.026
<i>You helped me
grow the hell up,</i>

24:45.111 --> 24:46.823
<i>and you took a bullet
out of my stomach.</i>

24:46.923 --> 24:48.142
<i>You paged me?</i>

24:48.401 --> 24:50.730
I did. I have a surgery.

24:50.815 --> 24:52.322
You're actually gonna let me
near a patient?

24:52.406 --> 24:53.689
You are the patient.

24:53.774 --> 24:55.332
Get in there and get
on that table. Oh...

24:55.416 --> 24:56.550
[ Sighs ]

24:56.635 --> 24:58.776
I don't need a reminder
of this thing.

24:58.861 --> 25:00.707
I'm gonna carry
that day around with me

25:00.792 --> 25:02.542
every day
for the rest of my life.

25:02.627 --> 25:04.548
I don't need a reminder
every time I look at you.

25:04.666 --> 25:07.816
And I'm tired [chuckles]
of bullying you,

25:07.901 --> 25:09.458
so I am asking you,

25:09.768 --> 25:13.533
please, get in there
and get your shirt off.

25:15.868 --> 25:17.620
<i>You protected Jo
from herself,</i>

25:17.705 --> 25:19.167
<i>and if I started
the whole list</i>

25:19.252 --> 25:21.064
<i>of everything
I learned from you,</i>

25:21.244 --> 25:22.448
<i>I would never stop writing.</i>

25:22.533 --> 25:24.549
<i>And right now my hand hurts.</i>

25:25.299 --> 25:27.049
<i>So just know this.</i>

25:27.292 --> 25:29.878
<i>It took me
a long time to say it,</i>

25:30.228 --> 25:32.595
<i>but I'm a good peds surgeon.</i>

25:33.885 --> 25:35.168
<i>I'm an okay guy.</i>

25:35.775 --> 25:37.298
<i>I'm still trying.</i>

25:37.916 --> 25:41.400
<i>But I'm a really
damn good surgeon.</i>

25:41.540 --> 25:43.488
- We got movement!
- And I don't mind saying it now

25:43.572 --> 25:45.642
because I didn't
figure it out myself.

25:46.384 --> 25:49.297
<i>You kicked my ass
and asked more of me than anyone</i>

25:49.382 --> 25:51.420
<i>and hired other teachers
who kicked my ass</i>

25:51.505 --> 25:52.647
<i>and asked more of me.</i>

25:52.732 --> 25:54.798
Karev, I hear that
you're the future of peds.

25:54.882 --> 25:57.588
Excuse me? - Yeah, a little birdie
named Bailey whispered it in my ear.

25:57.672 --> 25:59.521
I want you to work with me today so I
can see if she's right.

25:59.605 --> 26:00.605
What did she say?

26:00.732 --> 26:02.343
That you're the best babysitter
in the hospital.

26:02.427 --> 26:03.708
- Shut up.
- [ Chuckles ]

26:03.792 --> 26:05.498
Alex:
<i>And I know who I am.</i>

26:05.582 --> 26:09.053
<i>I'm not that guy with a million
Catherine Fox Awards on a shelf.</i>

26:09.138 --> 26:10.459
Goodbye, Mom.

26:10.544 --> 26:12.482
Bye.

26:13.021 --> 26:15.548
Bailey: A junkie dad,
a crackpot mom,

26:15.632 --> 26:18.878
and somehow Karev
still became a doctor.

26:18.962 --> 26:21.779
I'm not easily impressed,
but I'm impressed.

26:21.864 --> 26:23.874
Alex: <i>I became the guy you
trusted to run the hospital</i>

26:23.958 --> 26:24.912
<i>and keep your secrets.</i>

26:24.997 --> 26:26.668
<i>And now...</i>
It's okay.

26:26.752 --> 26:29.498
<i>...and now I'm a surgeon,
a friend,</i>

26:29.583 --> 26:32.717
<i>a father of two incredible kids
with Izzie Stevens,</i>

26:32.802 --> 26:36.088
<i>which I'm sure is breaking
[Chuckling] your brain.</i>

26:36.356 --> 26:38.207
<i>- But it's true.</i>
- Nothing!

26:38.529 --> 26:40.048
<i>I'm all these things.</i>

26:40.132 --> 26:41.548
She been out there
all day?

26:41.632 --> 26:43.838
<i>And by the way,
I have a shot</i>

26:43.922 --> 26:46.466
<i>at being Chief of Peds
at Shawnee County here,</i>

26:46.654 --> 26:49.201
<i>but I'm guessing
you're the last person</i>

26:49.286 --> 26:51.482
<i>I should put down as a rec
right now.</i>

26:53.042 --> 26:56.588
<i>Okay, look, the... the kids
keep asking for pizza sushi,</i>

26:56.672 --> 26:58.998
<i>and I have to go tell them
that's not a thing.</i>

26:59.082 --> 27:01.575
<i>And if I say any more
in this letter,</i>

27:02.042 --> 27:04.668
<i>there are going to be feelings
all over the place.</i>

27:05.044 --> 27:06.411
<i>Yours, not mine.</i>

27:07.008 --> 27:09.356
<i>And, really,
I'm just writing to say goodbye.</i>

27:10.510 --> 27:11.878
<i>And thanks.</i>

27:12.283 --> 27:13.597
<i>And that sounds lame and small</i>

27:13.682 --> 27:14.895
<i>compared to everything
you've done,</i>

27:14.979 --> 27:17.971
<i>but [sighs] there it is.</i>

27:19.526 --> 27:21.760
<i>Goodbye, and thanks.</i>

27:23.806 --> 27:25.647
<i>I love you, Dr. Bailey.</i>

27:27.900 --> 27:29.119
<i>Dr. Alex Karev.</i>

27:29.227 --> 27:35.557
[♪♪]

27:38.644 --> 27:42.068
- Richard, alcoholic.
- Hi, Richard.

27:43.481 --> 27:44.873
[ Sighs ]

27:46.333 --> 27:47.725
See one,

27:48.458 --> 27:49.770
do one,

27:50.333 --> 27:51.529
teach one.

27:52.825 --> 27:55.661
That's been the motto
of every hospital I run,

27:55.896 --> 27:58.680
every teacher I've loved.

27:59.091 --> 28:03.896
I loved being a surgeon,
saving lives,

28:04.333 --> 28:07.910
giving people back
their families,

28:08.912 --> 28:11.944
their loved ones,
and their friends.

28:12.044 --> 28:16.458
Giving them back to them
when all seemed lost.

28:17.354 --> 28:20.295
And I loved my students,
not because of ego...

28:20.380 --> 28:22.470
[ Motor whirring ]

28:22.554 --> 28:23.431
[ Snips ]

28:23.515 --> 28:25.350
I'm done.
I'm done! I'm done!

28:25.434 --> 28:29.890
<i>...but because it gave me that
same rush, that same feeling...</i>

28:29.974 --> 28:33.350
That's why I'm the chief.

28:34.084 --> 28:37.250
<i>It's like you're helping
to keep people alive,</i>

28:37.335 --> 28:39.429
keep families alive.

28:40.903 --> 28:43.724
And then this morning,
I wake up to a letter

28:43.841 --> 28:46.850
from a student of mine,
who, well,

28:46.934 --> 28:50.930
let's just say he's not the one
I would have put money down on.

28:51.014 --> 28:53.230
What happens, uh,
if I... if I take the exam

28:53.314 --> 28:55.520
for a second time
and I don't pass?

28:55.604 --> 28:58.420
You will no longer be a surgical
resident at Seattle Grace.

28:58.505 --> 28:59.880
Failing again
is not an option.

28:59.988 --> 29:01.970
- Alex: What's the big deal?
- Richard: Well, the big deal is you're...

29:02.054 --> 29:05.943
You're sweaty and you
[sniffs] and you smell.

29:06.028 --> 29:07.850
And you're not going
into my OR.

29:07.934 --> 29:09.194
What the hell's the matter
with you today?

29:09.278 --> 29:10.850
This is a teaching hospital,
okay?

29:10.935 --> 29:12.568
You were the chief
for 20 years.

29:12.653 --> 29:14.680
You're supposed to be
teaching your residents.

29:14.841 --> 29:17.100
Oh, I think I taught you
something today.

29:17.310 --> 29:20.230
You don't give up a
once-in-a-lifetime surgery,

29:20.314 --> 29:23.998
not for any reason,
not for anyone, not ever.

29:24.083 --> 29:26.020
But he... he did the work.

29:26.104 --> 29:29.180
Yeah.
He... He showed up.

29:29.264 --> 29:32.640
He... He stepped up.

29:32.880 --> 29:35.430
Became an excellent student,

29:35.514 --> 29:38.430
a stellar surgeon.
10 blade.

29:38.514 --> 29:40.100
Richard: <i>You're an underdog,
aren't you, Karev?</i>

29:40.184 --> 29:41.640
It's not that you don't
have the skills.

29:41.724 --> 29:42.930
You have the skills.

29:43.014 --> 29:46.100
But you're scrappy.
You're a fighter.

29:46.419 --> 29:48.060
I like that.

29:48.255 --> 29:49.600
I always root
for the underdog.

29:50.130 --> 29:52.208
A fine teacher.

29:53.121 --> 29:55.778
He was working
with the best of the best.

29:57.262 --> 30:00.769
But instead,

30:01.099 --> 30:03.498
he chose to abandon it all

30:03.583 --> 30:06.935
for who he says
is the woman he loves.

30:07.895 --> 30:11.442
And for the two children
they now have.

30:12.786 --> 30:16.420
You know, I wanted to
look him straight in the eye

30:16.505 --> 30:19.725
and yell at him and...
And tell him

30:19.810 --> 30:21.522
that he's made a mistake,

30:21.607 --> 30:23.950
that it feels like a mistake.

30:25.771 --> 30:27.680
I've been there before,
yeah.

30:27.942 --> 30:31.470
I've fallen in love with two
people at the same time,

30:31.555 --> 30:32.685
and...

30:35.232 --> 30:37.568
And I know all you can do
is go with what your...

30:37.653 --> 30:40.583
Your bones and your guts
and your heart tell you to.

30:40.700 --> 30:43.600
I wanted to grab him
and shake him and tell him,

30:43.684 --> 30:46.013
"Don't give it all away.

30:46.224 --> 30:48.935
Not now.
Not for... for this."

30:49.574 --> 30:50.849
[ Sighs ]

30:51.177 --> 30:54.942
But I missed my chance to watch
my own child grow into an adult.

30:56.511 --> 31:00.427
And I would give anything to
have those years with Maggie.

31:00.745 --> 31:02.388
I'd do anything.

31:04.231 --> 31:05.966
I guess, um...

31:07.356 --> 31:09.107
I just wanted
to say goodbye.

31:10.661 --> 31:12.521
I just wanted
to say goodbye.

31:12.724 --> 31:14.247
Hey, Dr. Webber.

31:14.519 --> 31:16.229
I-I didn't want to work here,
either.

31:16.314 --> 31:19.522
You know, at Grey-Sloan,
I inherited a-a legacy.

31:19.607 --> 31:21.326
Bailey's legacy,
your legacy.

31:21.411 --> 31:22.671
You know, I mean,
every choice I made,

31:22.755 --> 31:25.247
I heard your voice in my head...
"Don't settle. Do better."

31:25.394 --> 31:27.584
At Grey-Sloan,
failing was our last option.

31:27.669 --> 31:28.930
But here,
failure's the culture.

31:29.364 --> 31:30.470
But we can change that.

31:30.554 --> 31:32.140
Help me turn
this place around.

31:32.427 --> 31:34.140
Help me do the impossible.

31:34.224 --> 31:37.263
I wanted to say thank you
for helping me

31:37.354 --> 31:42.028
to be a better doctor,
better teacher.

31:42.855 --> 31:44.419
I mean, anything.

31:45.380 --> 31:46.592
[ Applause ]

31:46.677 --> 31:47.350
But he up and left...

31:47.434 --> 31:49.470
Karev! Do better!

31:49.554 --> 31:53.890
...with only a note
and an apology, and that's it,

31:54.162 --> 31:57.600
not considering that I might
want to say goodbye

31:57.771 --> 31:59.020
as a teacher...

31:59.104 --> 32:00.560
Watch your back,
Karev.

32:00.644 --> 32:02.680
I may decide to teach you
something tomorrow.

32:02.764 --> 32:03.662
[♪♪]

32:03.755 --> 32:05.309
Time of...

32:05.394 --> 32:06.717
...as a colleague...

32:06.802 --> 32:08.230
Time of death... 15:42.

32:08.314 --> 32:10.631
...as a friend.

32:11.173 --> 32:12.576
See one.

32:12.810 --> 32:14.350
Do one.

32:14.646 --> 32:16.302
Teach one.

32:17.054 --> 32:21.881
I've [sighs]
seen people leave.

32:22.332 --> 32:25.168
I've done the leaving.

32:25.716 --> 32:29.430
Woman: Richard! Richard!
Richard!

32:29.514 --> 32:31.319
Richard: I was gonna ask you
to be by my side

32:31.404 --> 32:32.256
for the rest of our lives.

32:32.341 --> 32:34.020
I'm not sorry
about a damn thing.

32:34.104 --> 32:37.520
[♪♪]

32:37.740 --> 32:41.216
And lately, it seems like
all the people I love just...

32:42.264 --> 32:44.318
...they just disappear.

32:45.834 --> 32:48.140
And...

32:48.677 --> 32:50.310
I can't...

32:50.638 --> 32:54.279
find a way to make it stop.

32:54.373 --> 32:57.434
[♪♪]

33:03.216 --> 33:05.437
Alex, if you want to
know how she is,

33:05.522 --> 33:07.513
you should just call her.

33:07.597 --> 33:08.757
You should call Izzie.

33:08.842 --> 33:09.781
[ Scoffs ] No.

33:09.866 --> 33:11.263
No, it's okay.

33:11.724 --> 33:12.882
No.

33:12.967 --> 33:15.553
I mean,
I-I-I don't need to call her.

33:15.975 --> 33:18.053
I know how she is.

33:18.413 --> 33:20.223
I mean, she's, uh...

33:20.428 --> 33:22.923
She's married
with three kids,

33:23.007 --> 33:28.553
and she lives somewhere,
I think, uh, kind of woodsy?

33:28.637 --> 33:30.383
[ Chuckles ]

33:30.467 --> 33:32.763
And she's a surgeon
and she goes to work every day,

33:32.847 --> 33:37.364
so she refuses to hire help,
so her house is always a mess.

33:38.276 --> 33:41.669
And it has Christmas decorations
all over it

33:41.754 --> 33:45.012
because she won't let
her husband take them down.

33:47.339 --> 33:48.552
It smells like muffins,

33:48.637 --> 33:50.864
and she's...

33:50.949 --> 33:52.359
She's smiling.

33:54.635 --> 33:57.671
When I picture her,
she's always smiling.

33:57.967 --> 34:01.598
I don't need to call her because
I want it to stay that way.

34:02.846 --> 34:07.176
I picture her
as happy as I am with you.

34:08.677 --> 34:10.422
You imagined
a whole life for her?

34:10.590 --> 34:13.223
Oh, yeah.
It's way better than wondering.

34:13.306 --> 34:16.263
[ Ingrid Michaelson's
"Turn to Stone" plays ]

34:16.347 --> 34:19.583
<i>- ♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh ♪
- Hi, Izzie Stevens. Washington.</i>

34:19.668 --> 34:22.473
Hi, Alex Karev. Iowa.

34:22.567 --> 34:23.771
What program are you in?

34:23.856 --> 34:25.672
- Surgery.
<i>- ♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh ♪</i>

34:25.757 --> 34:26.774
Seriously?

34:26.859 --> 34:27.904
Seriously.

34:28.167 --> 34:29.690
Morning, Dr. Model.

34:29.879 --> 34:30.882
Dr. Evil Spawn.

34:30.967 --> 34:33.382
- Ooh. Nice tat.
<i>- ♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh ♪</i>

34:33.467 --> 34:35.061
Do you ever wake up
in the morning and realize

34:35.145 --> 34:38.303
nobody likes you
and, I don't know, care?

34:38.387 --> 34:39.590
Oh.

34:40.177 --> 34:41.223
I think
somebody likes me.

34:41.306 --> 34:43.474
- What is she doing?
- [ Laughs ]

34:43.559 --> 34:45.963
She's hanging out
with Alex.

34:46.047 --> 34:48.263
[♪♪]

34:48.347 --> 34:51.154
<i>- ♪ Let's go to sleep with clearer heads ♪</i>
- What?

34:51.239 --> 34:53.114
There's a discussion
we could have

34:53.199 --> 34:55.279
if you wanted to have
one.

34:55.364 --> 34:57.092
I kissed you
with tongue...

34:57.177 --> 35:00.037
<i>- ♪ And hearts too big to fit our beds ♪</i>
- ...and I plan to do it again and again.

35:00.121 --> 35:01.801
Get used to it.

35:01.886 --> 35:02.903
Ow!

35:03.096 --> 35:04.342
Izzie:
I care about you.

35:04.427 --> 35:05.513
<i>♪ And maybe
we won't feel so alone ♪</i>

35:05.597 --> 35:07.383
And I'm not gonna stop
caring about you,

35:07.467 --> 35:09.013
no matter how hard
you push me away.

35:09.097 --> 35:10.696
Shut up
and get out of my room.

35:10.781 --> 35:11.963
No.

35:12.085 --> 35:14.512
- I care about you.
<i>- ♪ Before we turn to stone ♪</i>

35:14.597 --> 35:16.142
And I know
you care about me, too.

35:16.227 --> 35:17.723
It is not too late
for us.

35:17.807 --> 35:19.110
Admit that
you care about me, too.

35:19.194 --> 35:21.696
I know you do.
I care about you.

35:21.781 --> 35:23.486
<i>♪ And if you wait for someone else's
hand ♪</i> - I care about you.

35:23.570 --> 35:26.071
I care about you.
I care about you.

35:26.156 --> 35:28.093
I...

35:28.327 --> 35:31.164
<i>- ♪ Then you will surely fall down ♪</i>
- I think with you, you make me better.

35:31.248 --> 35:33.954
Oh! You make me
want to be better.

35:34.124 --> 35:35.723
You make me
want to be good.

35:36.147 --> 35:37.633
And I think I can.

35:37.717 --> 35:39.303
<i>♪ And if you wait for someone
else's hand</i> ♪ - With you, I think I can.

35:39.387 --> 35:41.055
And if you want to be scared,
that's okay.

35:41.140 --> 35:42.173
Just be scared with me.

35:42.258 --> 35:43.907
I don't want to be
the future of this hospital

35:43.991 --> 35:47.460
- if you're not there with me.
<i>- ♪ You'll fall ♪</i>

35:47.806 --> 35:53.092
<i>♪ You'll fall ♪</i>

35:53.177 --> 35:55.671
[ Defibrillator thumps ]

35:55.889 --> 35:57.828
I didn't know you still
felt that way about me.

35:57.913 --> 35:58.802
Me neither.

35:58.887 --> 36:00.673
[♪♪]

36:00.757 --> 36:03.616
<i>- ♪ I know that I am nothing new ♪</i>
- [ Laughing ] I love you.

36:04.522 --> 36:05.687
What?

36:05.772 --> 36:07.013
I love you.

36:07.171 --> 36:08.383
I freaking love you.

36:08.467 --> 36:10.430
I can totally see you
in ten years...

36:10.515 --> 36:12.118
<i>- ♪ There's so much more ♪</i>
- ...a little salt and pepper in your hair,

36:12.202 --> 36:15.383
- big-shot attending.
<i>- ♪ Than me and you ♪</i>

36:15.515 --> 36:17.117
You're gonna be
a rock star, Alex.

36:17.202 --> 36:18.223
Shut up.

36:18.307 --> 36:23.513
<i>♪ But, brother,
how we must atone ♪</i>

36:23.726 --> 36:25.383
I love you.

36:25.866 --> 36:31.553
<i>♪ Before we turn to stone ♪</i>

36:31.637 --> 36:33.923
<i>[♪♪]</i>

36:34.092 --> 36:40.179
<i>♪ Before we turn to stone ♪</i>

36:48.765 --> 36:50.370
You taking my spot
on the couch tonight?

36:50.455 --> 36:51.455
[ Scoffs ]

36:54.022 --> 36:55.263
Miranda, is...?

36:55.347 --> 36:57.923
Alex Karev
isn't coming back.

36:58.271 --> 37:00.030
Left his wife,

37:01.061 --> 37:03.123
his friends, his job.

37:04.130 --> 37:10.179
Alex Karev is now a father
of two with Izzie Stevens.

37:12.998 --> 37:16.592
And, if they take my
recommendation seriously,

37:16.677 --> 37:20.921
he'll soon be Chief of Peds
at Shawnee Memorial.

37:24.097 --> 37:25.804
What's this got to do
with Joey?

37:25.936 --> 37:27.593
[ Chuckles ]

37:27.677 --> 37:30.578
Now,
it is a matter of luck,

37:30.663 --> 37:35.303
of grace that Alex Karev
is who he is today.

37:35.851 --> 37:41.000
He could have just as easily
been lost to this world,

37:41.085 --> 37:42.723
aimless.

37:42.807 --> 37:46.343
But he survived his home,

37:46.741 --> 37:49.593
his family,
his foster homes

37:49.677 --> 37:51.593
and became a man,

37:52.093 --> 37:54.593
now a father,

37:55.452 --> 37:58.288
a fine surgeon by luck,

37:59.061 --> 38:00.804
by chance.

38:01.307 --> 38:02.710
[ Sighs ]

38:02.795 --> 38:06.461
Joey's future shouldn't
be a matter of chance.

38:06.546 --> 38:11.061
A child's future
can't be a matter of luck.

38:14.632 --> 38:15.999
Okay.

38:17.366 --> 38:18.803
"Okay"?

38:19.022 --> 38:20.827
Just like that? "Okay"?

38:22.217 --> 38:25.241
I just wanted to
talk about it.

38:25.741 --> 38:27.781
I mean, you and I,
look, we... we both make

38:27.866 --> 38:31.303
these big, sweeping decisions
without each other.

38:31.483 --> 38:34.133
You... You had a heart attack
and didn't tell me.

38:34.499 --> 38:36.757
You... You had a miscarriage
and shut me out.

38:36.850 --> 38:38.765
You... You change
careers like sweaters.

38:39.331 --> 38:41.960
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

38:43.319 --> 38:46.280
And I am down
for all of it. I...

38:47.085 --> 38:51.305
All the change and the easy
and the hard that comes with it.

38:51.390 --> 38:53.280
Of course Joey
should have you.

38:53.390 --> 38:54.673
Should have us.

38:54.757 --> 38:57.210
He should have a family.

38:57.387 --> 38:58.819
But...

39:00.047 --> 39:07.038
that family needs to learn to
talk to each other first, okay?

39:10.476 --> 39:12.272
I'm sorry.

39:12.637 --> 39:13.708
I know.

39:13.793 --> 39:15.293
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

39:19.046 --> 39:21.632
Congratulations,
Miranda.

39:21.717 --> 39:22.969
It's a boy.

39:23.054 --> 39:25.187
A teenage boy!

39:25.272 --> 39:26.673
[ Chuckles ]

39:26.757 --> 39:29.223
It's another boy.

39:29.452 --> 39:32.223
[ Plested's
"Beautiful & Brutal" plays ]

39:32.307 --> 39:36.013
[♪♪]

39:36.097 --> 39:37.673
<i>♪ I don't know what,
I don't know what ♪</i>

39:37.757 --> 39:39.633
♪ I don't know
what's happening ♪

39:39.717 --> 39:43.226
- You can quit hovering.
- I'm not hovering.

39:43.311 --> 39:45.763
<i>♪ I swallow the pain,
drink in your poison ♪</i> - I'm... deciding

39:45.847 --> 39:50.173
whether to come in or give you
space... <i>- ♪ Darling, it hurts so sweet ♪</i>

39:50.310 --> 39:52.882
<i>- ♪ I try to run, try to run ♪</i>
- ...or take you day drinking.

39:52.967 --> 39:54.883
<i>♪ But I come back again ♪</i>

39:55.130 --> 39:57.366
Okay, whiskey it is.

39:57.513 --> 39:59.531
<i>♪ I look in your eyes, don't have
a choice, yeah ♪</i> - [ Sighs ]

39:59.615 --> 40:00.802
[ Pager beeps ]

40:00.974 --> 40:03.748
- [ Sighs ]
<i>- ♪ You'll be the death of me ♪</i>

40:03.887 --> 40:06.171
Pierce is paging me
for a cecal bascule

40:06.256 --> 40:08.046
for one of
our cabbage patients.

40:08.131 --> 40:10.093
[♪♪]

40:10.177 --> 40:13.263
- Okay.
<i>- ♪ It'll cut you deep ♪</i>

40:13.356 --> 40:15.157
- Whiskey tonight.
<i>- ♪ It'll watch you bleed ♪</i>

40:15.451 --> 40:17.633
Today I am working.

40:17.717 --> 40:21.423
<i>♪ Nothing hits as hard
as when we touch ♪</i>

40:21.507 --> 40:26.162
<i>- ♪ How beautiful and brutal
is your love? ♪ - Link: You're my hero.</i>

40:26.318 --> 40:27.389
Mine, too.

40:27.474 --> 40:29.138
<i>We hold onto hope,</i>

40:30.169 --> 40:32.724
<i>thinking one small detail,</i>

40:32.824 --> 40:34.208
<i>one tiny piece of information</i>

40:34.293 --> 40:36.329
<i>will somehow
make things right,</i>

40:36.811 --> 40:37.990
<i>make it different,</i>

40:38.365 --> 40:40.263
<i>make it okay...</i>

40:40.763 --> 40:43.092
<i>stop the world
from spinning off its axis.</i>

40:43.240 --> 40:46.663
Mom, Uncle Alex said when
I finish my science project,

40:46.763 --> 40:48.177
I'm supposed to show him.

40:48.296 --> 40:49.514
Can you show me?

40:49.599 --> 40:51.116
He helped me
come up with it.

40:51.201 --> 40:52.633
It's a dog feeder.
See?

40:52.717 --> 40:54.319
When the dog walks
on this lever,

40:54.404 --> 40:57.046
the pulley tips
the bucket over and...

40:57.131 --> 40:59.210
[ Dog food pours ]
That is so smart!

40:59.295 --> 41:01.202
[ Laughs ]
All we need is a dog.

41:01.287 --> 41:03.303
[ Both laugh ]

41:03.388 --> 41:06.053
So, can I show him?

41:06.224 --> 41:09.963
Can we go and show Uncle Alex
right now, please?

41:10.138 --> 41:12.568
<i>- ♪ Don't care how hard I gotta suffer ♪</i>
- Um...

41:12.653 --> 41:13.923
[ Pats sofa ]
Come sit here.

41:14.007 --> 41:17.013
<i>♪ I'm waking up
in your covers ♪</i>

41:17.097 --> 41:20.173
<i>- ♪ Beautiful and brutal ♪</i>
- Your Uncle Alex loves you so much.

41:20.257 --> 41:21.599
<i>- ♪ Cuts you deep ♪</i>
- [ Laughs ]

41:21.684 --> 41:23.223
And I just got a letter
from him.

41:23.307 --> 41:25.178
<i>- ♪ It'll watch you bleed ♪</i>
- You did? - I did.

41:25.263 --> 41:26.383
<i>When the truth is...</i>

41:26.468 --> 41:28.224
<i>♪ Nothing hits
as hard as when we touch ♪</i>

41:28.315 --> 41:30.755
<i>...there's really
no good way to say goodbye.</i>

41:30.902 --> 41:35.842
<i>♪ How beautiful
and brutal is your love? ♪</i>
